More Obituaries for Arthur Ryan


Looking for an obituary for a different person with this name?












Arthur F. Ryan


Obituary
Condolences




























Arthur F. RyanAGE: 86 • MorristownArthur F. Ryan, age 86, of Morristown New Jersey passed from this life on February 12th, 2015. Arthur was born on March 13th, 1928 in Cranford New Jersey, the son of Lawrence and Monica Ryan. He had three brothers, Larry, Bob and David. He spent his childhood in Cranford and the summers in Atlantic City with Uncle Leo and Aunt Kitty. He graduated from Cranford High School, and then served time in the army in Europe during the Korean conflict. He married Mary Ann Kaminski in 1955 and had three children: Greg, deceased, Larry and Martha. After the army he spent many years in the publishing industry, working for Hammond Map Company, Times Life Publishing, Macmillian Publishing and Simon and Schuster where he was a vice president of sales and promotions. He owned his own company, Ryan Promotion Agency from 1983 until he retired in 1995. He loved to travel and has visited all of the lower 48 states and many countries in Western Europe. He was an avid golfer and played into his retirement.He is preceded in death by his parents Lawrence G. Ryan and Monica Ryan, his step mother Anne Ryan, his brothers Lawrence Ryan and Robert Ryan, and his son Gregory Ryan. He is survived by his wife of 60 years, Mary Ann Ryan, his brother David and his two children, Martha and Larry, daughters-in-law Shelly and Patty, and his three grand children: Sarah, Ean and Sam.A Mass of Christian Burial will be celebrated at the Church of the Assumption, Morristown, NJ Tuesday at 10:00AM. Memorial visitation at the Doyle Funeral Home(www.doylefh.com) 106 Maple Ave., Morristown on Monday from 2-6PM.



Published in Daily Record on Feb. 15, 2015


